						<div class="postbody">Steam's new <a href="http://www.examiner.com/article/steam-big-picture-mode-launches-today-takes-on-consoles-with-minimalist-ui" class="postlink">Big Picture</a> front-end for home theater PCs introduces the flower, a text input method designed for gamepads. Eight groups of four letters are arranged in a circle. Pressing and releasing a direction or long-pressing it moves the cursor; holding a direction and pressing a button enters that letter corresponding to the button's position within the direction's group.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">,-------+-------+-------.<br />|&nbsp; &nbsp;\&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;B&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;F&nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />| ;&nbsp; &nbsp;&amp; | A&nbsp; &nbsp;C | E&nbsp; &nbsp;G |<br />|&nbsp; &nbsp;_&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;D&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;H&nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />+-------+-------+-------+<br />|&nbsp; &nbsp;Z&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;J&nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />| Y&nbsp; &nbsp;? |&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;| I&nbsp; &nbsp;K |<br />|&nbsp; &nbsp;!&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;L&nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />+-------+-------+-------+<br />|&nbsp; &nbsp;V&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;R&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;N&nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />| U&nbsp; &nbsp;W | Q&nbsp; &nbsp;S | M&nbsp; &nbsp;O |<br />|&nbsp; &nbsp;X&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;T&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;P&nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />`-------+-------+-------'<br />L: Capital&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;R: Numbers<br /></div><br />For example, on the Super NES, you'd type &quot;assembly&quot; as Up+Y, Down+A, Down+A, Up+Right+Y, Down+Right+Y, Up+X, Right+B, Left+Y. But I wonder how to adapt it to something like the NES that has fewer convenient buttons.</div>

