						<div class="postbody">jedahan in #nesdev pointed me to a <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pkr2uv9X-8k" class="postlink">video of Steam's flower in action</a>, as well as describing how to make flower work on an NES controller. Instead of A, B, X, and Y, as one might do with a Super NES or bigger controller, one might use B, BB, A, and AA. Then A, B, Select, and Start for space, backspace, page change, and accept.</div>

