					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you don't want to use a full onscreen keyboard, you can use an onscreen multitap cellphone keyboard. I'm going to take a random stab in the dark and say that most people know how to type on those already. You can even be fancy and use T9 predictive input, which is where it's only one keypress per letter, and based on the sequence you're pressing the buttons in, the software guesses what word you're trying to type in, so &quot;hello&quot; would be 43556 instead of 44 33 555 555 666.<br /><br />In the end, I don't think you can do anything other than have an onscreen representation of your input method, unless you're literally using a keyboard.</div>

